docs.lead_paragraph: KNOXVILLE, Tenn., April 14. -- The Presidential train arrived at Roanoke, Va., at 8:50 o'clock this morning, having made the run from Washington on exact schedule time. There were no special incidents on the route. A brief stop was made at Blue Ridge, where a crowd gathered at the station and enjoyed the spectacle of the Chief Magistrate of their country and his family at breakfast.

docs.lead_paragraph: From our Special Correspondent, whose inleresting story, written on board the big ship, may be found in another column of this paper, and is amply confirmed by tile accounts of the London papers, we learn that the Great Eastern had left her moorings, and that her performances, so far as opportunity had been afforded, fully met the most sanguine expectations.
